• Footprinting and Reconnaissance :-

The process of gathering data from publicly accessible sources on a target company, 
network, website, or person is known as "footprinting." It is the initial stage of 
penetration testing and ethical hacking.

• Footprinting Methodology :-

A standard footprinting methodology consists of:
Step 1: Target Identification
Identify the organization or website.
Step 2: Information Gathering
Collect public information.
Step 3: DNS Enumeration
Gather DNS records.
Step 4: Network Discovery
Identify IP addresses and routes.
Step 5: Website Analysis
Analyze website technologies.
Step 6: Documentation
Prepare a report.  

• Footprinting through Search Engines :-

Millions of webpages are indexed by search engines. Google Dorks assist in finding particular information.

